# Day 2 â€“ Basic navigation and RTFM

## Goal
Build confidence navigating the Linux file system from the command line. Practice creating, moving, and deleting files and directories. Learn how to read and search command documentation using built in tools.

## Environment
- Local machine: macOS
- Remote system: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS on Azure VM
- Access method: SSH

## Evidence (screenshots)
- `day2-navigation-pwd-cd-ls.png`
- `day2-mkdir-touch-mv-rm.png`
- `day2-rtfm-man-apropos.png`

## Tasks completed

### 1. Navigate the file system

pwd
cd ~
ls


### 2. List directory contents

ls
ls -a

### 3. Create files and directories

mkdir test
touch file


### 4. Move, copy, and delete

mv file test/
cd test
mv file my-first-file
cp my-first-file my-second-file
ls
rm my-first-file
cd ~
rm -r test
ls


### 5. RTFM, manuals, and search

man pwd
apropos list


